    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Eustis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27,
                                        1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Submit to French lawyer of first rank on whose impartiality you can
                                rely Waller record inclosed in yours of June 27, and get full
                                written opinion upon questions whether court was lawfully organized
                                and had jurisdiction and whether trial and sentence and all the
                                proceedings <pb facs="0358" n="298" xml:id="pg_298"/> were or were
                                not according to law; in other words, whether judgment and sentence
                                were valid upon their face without reference to the other.
                                Supplement with written views upon same questions of law, and
                                forward as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
